Load the airbnb data

data(nyc_airbnb)

questions

How many rentals are there? Of what type? In what places? Is price correlated with review scores? which neighborhood is most popular? Most expensive? Which neighborhood has the highest reviews? Is availability related to price? is room type related to neighborhood? is length of stay related to neighborhood group (borough)?

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(star = review_scores_location / 2)

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(neighbourhood_group == "Manhattan", price <= 1000) %>% 
  mutate(neighbourhood = fct_reorder(neighbourhood, price)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood, y = price)) +
  #summarize(mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE))
  geom_point() +
  coord_flip()

Price vs location

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(price < 500) %>% 
  sample_n(5000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long,  color = price)) +
  geom_point()

retry leaflet map

pal <- colorNumeric("magma", nyc_airbnb %>% pull(star))
nyc_airbnb %>% 
  drop_na(star) %>% 
  sample_n(5000) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(~lat, ~long, radius = 1, color = ~pal(star))
pal = colorNumeric("viridis", NULL)
nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(price < 500) %>% 
  sample_n(1000) %>% 
  mutate(
    lables = str_c("<b>Price:", price, "</b><br>Stars:", star)
  ) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  #addTiles() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>%
